    <div align="left" id="post_message_529892">Snibbs - I was walking along a saw a couple of asura fall from high above me, it was the only way i found it.  I'd love to try the secret boss, but currently only 13 and won't be able to play as I'll be away all Labor Day weekend.<br />
<br />
Sillis - <br />
<b>Is the PvE actually enjoyable or garbage like DAoC?</b>  The PvE game is quite well done.  There are quest hubs (heart locations) where you can pretty much do anything there (kill stuff, talk to people, do other activities) to fulfill the heart needs and complete that little area.  There are also some neat dynamic events that pop up randomly and if you follow them all the way through it usually ends with a mini-boss.  Also, you get exp for anything and everything; someone have something at half health and you come in and help kill it? You both get full exp and separate loot.  You get exp for gathering and crafting as well.  Also, they've created personal storylines which change depending on the background choices you chose during character creation. These are personal instances and remind me of SWTOR's personal character stories.<br />
<b><br />
Twitchy or more laid back?</b>  I would say that combat is active.  You are better off moving around, dodging attacks, and switching your weapon set in mid-fight because it makes it easier on you.  It takes a little bit to get used to.  Since I've gotten a better feel for it, it makes you wonder how games never played this way before.  Just watch how far you kite/circle strafe mobs as it's a lot easier to pull add this way.  You can just stand there and swing, but it'll end up being a lot harder of a fight.<br />
<b><br />
Can each class solo effectively?</b>  Yes, each class has several loadouts that are very solo friendly and a couple that are more for groups/multiple players.  So far I haven't found one profession (class) that can't solo well.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
<br>
<table width="100%%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
