</div>Banning your most rabid players is dumb.  Bans should be reserved for people who are repeatedly, actively hacking.  Exploiting a game error, to me, is the game designer's problem.  Extreme Banning of players is lazy and short-sighted and a sign of poor game management.  Players should never be required to determine what is intended versus what is not intended.  It doesn't matter what the &quot;exploit&quot; is, if its in the game then players should assume it is supposed to be in the game.  The game designer should fix the exploit and move on, not punish players for trying to get ahead within the game system.<br />
<br />
These bans make me think Guild Wars is run by this guy.<br />
<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T-jXe0x4YdM" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T-jXe0x4YdM</a></div>
