    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_530245">Things like this screw up economies, especially new ones that still have one leg broken with the trading post taking so long to get going. Anet took a hard stance because of this.  Just like with the bannings for acting like a **** in chat channels (vulgarity, hate speech, etc), or vulgar names. They have shown over and over they care more about the game than players that act like dicks.<br />
<br />
The players that took advantage of these situations by definition realized it was something that gave them a large edge compared to everything else they could do. So you cannot say 'how should we know what is intended or not' It clearly was out of the ordinary, otherwise no one would have did it hundreds or thousands of times.<br />
<br />
Taking this stance at launch is important, much like dealing with children.. which lets be honest anon people online act like.  I haven't seen anything like general chat in Orgrimmar or the Barrens in game and I like that.</div>
