</div>Hate speech and vulgarity are not the same thing a built-in game system to your own advantage.  Also, what game economies have been screwed up in the past by these sorts of things?  And would banning the people involved be a better fix for the economy than lesser punishments such as exchanging the earned income with an alternate currency or just flat out deleting it.  There are clearly many 1000s of players right now.  To suggest that these karma exploits would ruin the game economy and that banning said players fixes it doesn't hold water.<br />
<br />
<div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
