</div>Your logic is flawed. You seem to be saying players should not take advantage of situations that give them a large edge.  Will players be banned for choosing a class or build that is superior to others because it gives them a &quot;large edge&quot;?  There are several things people do hundreds or thousands of times as compared to similar options.  A superior options will ALWAYS exist. Its foolish to force players to determine which superior options are supposed to exist and which are not.  When the game developer makes a mistake the onus is on them to fix them, not the player to avoid the errors.<br />
<br />
What Anet did is tantamount to a bar manager kicking someone out for accepting a drink that was overly strong.  &quot;You can obviously tell that drink was too strong, but you never sent it back.  You're a scumbag! GET OUT!&quot;<br />
<br />
The customer is both examples just accepts something given to them that is likely better than they initially anticipated, the don't deserve punishment for someone else's mistake.<br />
<br />
<div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
